* 2000&amp;nbsp;– Nominated [[National Television Awards]], UK, Most Popular Comedy Performer for ''Da Ali G Show''
* 2000&amp;nbsp;– Won TV Quick Award, TV Personality of the Year for ''Da Ali G Show''
* 2001&amp;nbsp;– Won BAFTA TV Award, Best Comedy (Programme or Series) for ''Da Ali G Show'' (shared)
* 2001&amp;nbsp;– Won BAFTA TV Award, Best Comedy Performance for ''Da Ali G Show''
* 2003&amp;nbsp;– Nominated [[Emmy]] Award, Outstanding Non-Fiction Program (Alternative) for ''Da Ali G Show'' (shared)
* 2003&amp;nbsp;– Nominated Emmy Award, Outstanding Writing for Non-Fiction Programming for ''Da Ali G Show'' (shared)
* 2004&amp;nbsp;– Nominated Golden Satellite Award, Best Performance by an Actor in a Series, Comedy or Musical for ''Da Ali G Show''
* 2005&amp;nbsp;– Nominated Emmy Award, Outstanding Variety, Music or Comedy Series for ''Da Ali G Show'' (shared)
* 2005&amp;nbsp;– Nominated Emmy Award, Outstanding Writing for a Variety, Music or Comedy Program for ''Da Ali G Show'' (shared)
* 2006&amp;nbsp;– Won Ronnie Barker Award&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news | url=http://www.hellomagazine.com/celebrities/2006/12/14/borat-comedy-awards/ | access-date=9 June 2009 | title=Sacha leaves Borat behind as he steps out with Isla |work=Hello! | date=14 December 2006}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* 2007&amp;nbsp;– Won MTV Movie Award for Best Kiss alongside Will Ferrell in ''[[Talladega Nights: The Ballad of Ricky Bobby]]''
* 2012&amp;nbsp;– Won British Comedy Award, Outstanding Achievement Award.&lt;ref name=&quot;lifetime award&quot;/&gt;
*2019&amp;nbsp;– Nominated [[Golden Globe]] Award, Best Actor – Television Series Musical or Comedy for ''Who Is America?''
*2019&amp;nbsp;– Nominated [[Directors Guild of America]] Award, Outstanding Directorial Achievement in Variety/Talk/News/Sports – Regularly Scheduled Programming for ''Who Is America?'' (shared)
*2019&amp;nbsp;– Nominated Emmy Award, Outstanding Variety Sketch Series for ''Who Is America?'' (shared)
*2019&amp;nbsp;– Nominated Emmy Award, Outstanding Directing for a Variety Series for ''Who Is America?'' (shared)
*2019 – Nominated Emmy Award for Outstanding Picture Editing for Variety Programming for ''Who Is America?'' (shared)
* 2019&amp;nbsp;– Won International Leadership Award from ''[[Anti Defamation League]]''&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web|url=https://www.adl.org/news/article/sacha-baron-cohens-keynote-address-at-adls-2019-never-is-now-summit-on-anti-semitism|title=Sacha Baron Cohen's Keynote Address at ADL's 2019 Never Is Now Summit on Anti-Semitism and Hate|website=Anti-Defamation League|language=en|access-date=24 November 2019}}&lt;/ref&gt;

